	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=175859><span id=Administrator>Fleven the Stupendous</span></a><br><b><span id=Administrator>Administrator</span></b><br><span id=notbold>122 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.59]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>If you use a solvent to remove any augmentation, even this one, the augmentation is destroyed.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, if you have already completed the <a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2641 target=akztarg>Adventurer's Stone</a> quest, you can obtain a new one simply by hailing certain NPCs in any of the Wayfarers camps.  You may then add the new stone to the charm of your choice.  The stats are tied to your success in LDoN adventures, not to the stone itself, so destroying an old stone and getting a new one won't affect the stats.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Dec  2 17:58:22 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
