	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=148806><span id=Scholar>tjtassell</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>51 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.14]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>From the Adventure Flags quest description.<br><br>-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-<br><br>Short version <br><br>When you load Lost Dungeons of Norrath and enter the game for the first time, you will receive a &quot;mysterious message&quot; telling you to go back to your home town. If you are not sure what town you started in, you can also go to the Rathe Mountains gypsy camp or the NE corner of Western Karana. Once you arrive there, you will receive another &quot;mysterious message&quot; telling you to find a specific NPC. You need to find the person mentioned and hail him. He will tell you about the wayfarer camps and mention 5 more NPC's - one per camp. Head to a camp and talk to the NPC there and he will ask you some questions. Answer them and you will get flagged to use the adventure system and the Magus teleports that take you from camp to camp. <br><br>Answers: <br><br>Question <br>1: adventures <br>2: favor journal <br>3: Morden Rasp <br>4: Farstones <br><br>-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-<br><br>NOTE: You don't need to answer the first 3 questions. You can just say Farstones when they ask you the first question.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
