	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=196678><span id= >rgjmidgets</span></a><br><span id=notbold>21 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.25]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>In order to get 500 successes in one month you would have to win 17 adventures every day...I wouldn't exactly classify that as 'in between &quot;typical&quot; and &quot;hardcore&quot;' playing, especially because that means spending 25 hours a day in dungeons.<br><br>Please excuse a bit of rounding because of a rediculous amount of decimal places.<br><br>500wins/30days = 16.666<br>16.666wins * 1.5hours = 24.999hours<br><br>24.999hours/day is not only more than hardcore, it's called impossible. Even to do it in 2 months would require 8.333wins per day, and 12.5hours per day.<br><br><br>1 months: 16.666 wins per day = 24.999hours per day<br>2 months: 8.333 wins per day = 12.5hours per day<br>4 months: 4.15 wins per day = 6.2hours per day<br>6 months: 2.75 wins per day = 4.2hours per day<br><br>Ok, then add time for finding a group and getting ready to enter the dungeon, and you will see that it will take atleast 4 months from release before we start seeing more than a few people with maxxed LDoN charms. So, thanks for your assinine estimations, but you are WAY off.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sat Oct&nbsp;&nbsp;4 16:44:14 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
